          helping SPAI to win an SP Excellence Award in its first year.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Conscript Soldier at the Digital and Intelligence Service, Singapore Armed Forces"
      subtitle="From October 2023 to Present at Singapore Armed Forces, Singapore"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
        <li>
          Attained the platoon best trainee award in the Signals Institute
          vocational training course.
        </li>
        <li>
          Currently working on LLM agent workflows for automating work within my DIS unit.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Co-Founder at Flora Softworks"
      subtitle="From February 2023 to Present at Flora Softworks, Singapore"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
        <li>
          Flora is a tech startup that builds software to help organisations
          manage their information, with our primary product being an enterprise
          search application.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed a custom search engine using Elasticsearch, and a
          microservice architecture using Jina and MongoDB, to enable
          organisations to index and search through their data sources.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed unit tests for the AI microservices using Pytest, and also
          set up a Kubeflow pipeline on Vertex AI for running evaluation of our
          neural search engine using BEIR.
        </li>
        <li>
          Trained a custom object detection model using MMYOLO for document
          layout detection, applying techniques like knowledge distillation to
          improve inference speed by four times while also improving mean
          average precision (mAP) from 0.41 to 0.5 (a 21.95% improvement).
        </li>
        <li>
          Deployed the application on Google Cloud Platform and Firebase, and
          also performed on-premise deployment as part of a trial run for a
          client.
        </li>
        <li>
          Used OpenTelemetry in combination with Prometheus and Grafana to track
          and monitor the performance of the application, helping to identify
          and resolve memory leaks and bottlenecks.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Intern at Defence Science and Technology Agency"
      subtitle="From September 2022 to February 2023 at Defence Science and Technology Agency, Singapore"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
        <li>
          Core developer of the AI App Store project, an in-house platform built
          using Vue.js and FastAPI for AI developers to publish and share their
          models in the form of model cards, and deploy containers as KNative
          services through a GUI interface.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed API endpoints to enable the managing of services in a
          Kubernetes cluster through the app, as well as integration with the
          ClearML platform.
        </li>
        <li>
          Developed a custom WYSIWYG editor using the TipTap library, enabling
          the insertion of editable Plotly.js graphs within the markup.
        </li>
        <li>
          Wrote and maintained unit tests, and established automated testing
          through a CI pipeline deployed on GitHub Actions, resulting in a more
          reliable and robust application.
        </li>
        <li>
          Set up Helm charts, documentation and deployed the project on a
          Kubernetes cluster for use internally by two departments within DSTA.
        </li>
        <li>
          Contributed to a separate team project where I developed microservices
          for a prototype real time video analytics pipeline, integrating models
          like YOLOv5 and ByteTrack, using PyTorch, OpenCV, Triton Inference
          Server and Apache Kafka.
        </li>
      </ul>
